{"sections":[],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This backend supports Linux, macOS and Windows (maybe?), but its support for non-Linux platforms is significantly worse than ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","isActive":true},{"text":"â€˜s (due to underlying Gtk 3 issues). Even on Linux, itâ€™s recommended to use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","isActive":true},{"text":" over Gtk3Backend where possible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"warning","type":"aside","name":"Warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Non-Linux Gtk3Backend support is not a priority of this backend, and should only be used during development (e.g. to test your Linux UI natively on a Mac). There are multiple better choices of backend available on each non-Linux platform.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"System-dependencies","level":2,"text":"System dependencies"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you can use Gtk3Backend you must install the required system dependencies for your platform.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Linux","level":3,"text":"Linux"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["sudo apt install libgtk-3-dev"],"syntax":"sh"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 1: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"installing Gtk 3 dev on an apt-based Linux distro"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are on a non-apt distro and the Gtk3Backend requirements end up differing significantly from the requirements stated above, please open a GitHub issue or PR so that we can improve the documentation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"macOS","level":3,"